<TITLE> Police catch JMB man convicted of 2005 bombings </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, July 7 (bdnews24.com)Rajshahi police have arrested fugitive militant Najmul Haq Tuhin, a member of the banned group Jamatul Mujahideen Bangladesh who faces a 30-year sentence for involvement in the August 2005 bombings in Joypurhat. Locals informed police of Tuhin's presence at Sepaipara, after coming to know of his identity as a JMB member, Rajpara Police Station officer-in-charge Afzal Hossain told bdnews24.com Tuesday. Police arrested the 28-year-old fugitive from a house in the Sepaipara area on Monday evening. Tuhin, originally from Harail village in Joypurhat district's Sadar Upazila, was produced in a Rajshahi court Tuesday morning, said Hossain. "He was sent straight to jail." The banned Islamist outfit JMB launched a series of bomb attacks in the northern town of Joypurhat on Aug 17, 2005, which targeted the central mosque square at Pachur roundabout as well as a bus terminal and fish market. A rickshaw driver was killed in the bomb explosion at the fish market. bdnews24.c
